The paper deals with lower bounds for memory-bounded algorithms in the streaming model, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The second result specifically deals with the security of Goldreich's pseudorandom generator, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses techniques from time-space trade-offs, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
